# Tailwind CSS v4 — Do/Don't

## Do (v4 setup)
- Import once in CSS: add `@import "tailwindcss";` to [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css)
- Use PostCSS plugin in [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs): `plugins: ["@tailwindcss/postcss"]`
- Configure in CSS, not JS: define tokens in `@theme { ... }` (no config file)
- Use automatic class detection (no content array). If needed, add sources with `@source "./path"` in CSS.

## Prefer (new APIs)
- Gradients: `bg-linear-*`, plus `/oklch`; new `bg-conic-*`, `bg-radial-*`
- Container queries in core: `@container`, `@max-*`, `@min-*`
- Variants: `starting:*`, `not-*`, `in-*`, `descendant`, `open:` (popover)
- 3D transforms: `transform-3d`, `rotate-x-*`, `rotate-y-*`, `translate-z-*`, etc.
- Dynamic values: `grid-cols-N`, spacing via `--spacing` (e.g., `w-17`, `mt-8`)
- Colors: OKLCH palette; opacity via `/` or `color-mix()`

## Don’t (outdated in v4)
- Don’t create `tailwind.config.*` or a `content` array
- Don’t use `@tailwind base; @tailwind components; @tailwind utilities` — use `@import "tailwindcss"`
- Don’t add `postcss-import` (v4 has built-in import support)
- Don’t install `@tailwindcss/container-queries` (now core)
- Don’t prefer `bg-gradient-*` — use `bg-linear-*`

## Minimal snippet
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@theme {
  --font-sans: ui-sans-serif, system-ui;
  --color-brand-500: oklch(0.72 0.13 260);
}
@source "./components";
```

## Notes
- We use bun in this repo; replace npm/npx with `bun`/`bunx`.
- Keep using PostCSS in Next.js; Vite plugin is optional and not used here.

# Tailwind v4 Dark Mode

**CRITICAL**: Tailwind v4 requires explicit dark mode variant configuration.

## Required Setup

Add this line immediately after `@import "tailwindcss";` in `app/globals.css`:

```css
@custom-variant dark (&:is(.dark *));
```

Without this, `dark:` prefix classes will not work.

## Usage

Once configured, use standard dark mode syntax:

```tsx
className="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 text-black dark:text-white"
```
